SIMPLE: only
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Only
<hw>On"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>only</ets>,
<ets>anly</ets>, <ets>onlich</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦amac⟧nlic</ets>, i.e.,
onelike. See <er>One</er>, <er>and Like</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One alone; single; <as>as, the <ex>only</ex> man
present; his <ex>only</ex> occupation.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Alone in its class; by itself; not associated with
others of the same class or kind; <as>as, an <ex>only</ex>
child</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence,</specif> <mark>(figuratively)</mark>:
<def>Alone, by reason of superiority; preeminent; chief.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Motley's the <xex>only</xex> wear.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Only</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Only
<hw>On"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Only</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In one manner or degree; for one
purpose alone; simply; merely; barely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And to be loved himself, needs <qex>only</qex> to be known.</q>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>So and no otherwise; no other than; exclusively;
solely; wholly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧She being <xex>only</xex> wicked.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every imagination . . . of his heart was <qex>only</qex> evil.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. vi. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Singly; without more; <as>as,
<ex>only</ex>-begotten</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Above all others; particularly.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His most <qex>only</qex> elected mistress.</q>
<rj><qau>Marston.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Only</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Only
<hw>On"ly</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <def>Save or except (that); -- an
adversative used elliptically with or without <xex>that</xex>, and
properly introducing a single fact or consideration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He might have seemed some secretary or clerk . . . <qex>only</qex>
that his low, flat, unadorned cap . . . indicated that he belonged to
the city.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onocerin</ent>⟦br⟧
